YAML::PP::Schema::Env

This schema extends YAML::PP with a !ENV tag which can be used to
interpolate environment variables when loading YAML data or files.

To install, use

    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make test
    make install

Or just use any of the both CPAN installer commands:

    cpan YAML::PP::Schema::Env
    cpanm YAML::PP::Schema::Env

After installation, the following command may be used to read the
documentation:

    perldoc YAML::PP::Schema::Env

The repository can be found at
https://github.com/eserte/yaml-pp-schema-env
